                </app></p>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p/>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
             <p>We have here a list of names. The lettering and display look like those in some lists of ephebes. As to the depth of the panel (if we really have it here) the most similar item would be 
             <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr103800</ref>, but comparing the squeezes shows that they differ both in spacement and depth of characters.</p>
             <p>The faint traces of a final sigma at line 4 induces to restore nominatives, but this is not quite sure. Apart from Damatrios, which seems rather certain at line 5, we are only able to guess parts of 
                 names: in -kritos (or Krito-) at line 2 and in -ippos (or Hipp-) at line 6, the preferred readings being more plausible if the display was columnar.</p>
            </div></body>
